msContents.summary: Old Swedish Legal Manuscript. The manuscript consists mainly of legal texts but annalistic notes concerning Swedish history, recipes, etc. also occur.

Annalistic Notes Concerning the History of Sweden
msItem.note: The notes concerning the years 1521-69 are in Swedish and the ones concerning the years 1533-50 are in Latin.

foliation.p: The manuscript has been foliated on the recto pages.

condition.p: The number of chapters have been damaged due to cutting. The blank pages 104r and 103v have been glued together. Pieces of white paper have been pasted to the lower parts of 101v and 102v, apparently to delete some of the text.

handNote.p: This first contemporary hand occurs on ff. 1r-42r:5.
This second contemporary hand occurs on ff. 42r-103r.
The third hand is from the sixteenth century and occurs on f. 103v.
Thr fourth hand is also from the sixteenth century and occurs on ff. 111r-113v.

decoNote.p: The manuscript has red rubrics, initials, chapter numbers and runnings titles.
